public Set<Integer> getIdentifierTypes()
methods.comment:
* Returns the list of identifier types that satisfy the filter. * *

If the program list entry contains at least one identifier of the type * listed, it satisfies this condition. Empty list means no filtering on * identifier type. * * @return the set of accepted identifier types, must not be modified

methods.name: public Set<ProgramSelector.Identifier> getIdentifiers()
methods.comment:
* Returns the list of identifiers that satisfy the filter. * *

If the program list entry contains at least one listed identifier, * it satisfies this condition. Empty list means no filtering on identifier. * * @return the set of accepted identifiers, must not be modified

methods.name: public boolean areCategoriesIncluded()
methods.comment:
* Checks, if non-tunable entries that define tree structure on the
         * program list (i.e. DAB ensembles) should be included.
         *
         * @see ProgramSelector.Identifier#isCategoryType()

methods.name: public boolean areModificationsExcluded()
methods.comment:
* Checks, if updates on entry modifications should be disabled. * *

If true, 'modified' vector of ProgramListChunk must contain list * additions only. Once the program is added to the list, it's not * updated anymore.
